headline: Archer-Daniels-Midland (NYSE:ADM) Misses Q4 CY2025 Revenue Estimates
summary: Agricultural supply chain giant Archer-Daniels-Midland (NYSE:ADM) fell short of the markets revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales falling 13.7% year on year to $18.56 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.87 per share was 9.2% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: ADM: Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The average estimate of three analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of 83 cents per share. The agribusiness giant posted revenue of $18.56 billion in the period, which did not meet Street forecasts. Three analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $22.31 billion.
